How to set up UBR10k to generate downstream traffic to PB:

- set up ip address for controller (used as src IP in packets to EQAM)
- set up ip address for the rf channel (used as dst IP in packets to EQAM)
- set up ip address for the wideband channel (so we know how to destinate
  the WAN traffic to the wideband group)

WB interface: int cable 3/0/0:0
  Number after : is the wideband channel number
Need to assign a IP and subnet mask for this logical WB interface.

Then when the ubr10K receives a packet destinated to a ip-address in the same
subnet, it will be sent to the wideband channel.


To generate wideband traffic, continuous ping can be used.

